description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;As the Planning (EU Exit) Operations Manager within the South West Regional Operations Centre, the post holder will work as part of a dynamic team in delivering an effective service supporting local organisations across the Region to maintain a high level of preparedness and delivery for CoVid-19, Winter and EU Exit Transition. The post holder will be responsible for ensuring the smooth management and delivery of the Planning (EU Exit) Team operational activity, including:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Provide effective and flexible management of daily operations and incidents arising to support the delivery of ROC objectives.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ensure the welfare of staff groups through daily check in support calls (team huddles)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;the effective and co-ordinated flow of information in and out of the Planning(EU Exit) Team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Provide effective and timely briefings to appropriate staff groups, ensuring key information and updates are cascaded as required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Support the Planning (EU Exit) Shift Leader in ensuring that the Planning (EU Exit) Team is appropriately resourced across all roles, flagging additional resource requirements should demand require it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;Support and undertake activities/ tasks as required by the Planning (EU Exit) Shift Leader.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Planning (EU Exit) Operations Manager will generally work covering a variety of flexible shift patterns 7 days a week, flexing between 8 hour days and 12 hour days dependent on activity level. The weekend working requirements will be undertaken on a rota basis, unless volunteers are found to regularly work at the weekend. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The reason for this fixed term contract is a short term time limited project. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Tom Rossiter&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Head of ROCE&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: tom.rossiter@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
